						<summary>

						<p>East wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Nīlakaṇṭhēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Viruppaṇa-uḍaiyar, son of Hariyaṇa-uḍaiyar: naka 1314: 1392 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The details of date viz., Āṅgīra, Vṛiśchika •• 8, Friday and Magha regularly correspond to 1392 A.D., November 8. The <hi rend="italic">paksha</hi> intended was <hi rend="italic">bahuḷa.</hi></p>						

						<p>This incomplete epigraph records the grant of lands in Tirumaṇi in Poṉṉūr-paṟṟu by one Rāmadēvarāyaṉ, at the instance of Śivadēvar for maintaining a perpetual lamp, worship, food-offerings and repairs to the deity Kaṟaikaṇṭīśvaram-uḍaiya-nāyaṉār of Viḍāl in Poṉṉūr-paṟṟu in Śiṅgapura-nāḍu in ••••• kūṟṟam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḷa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

						</summary>
